Define a class to represent a bank account. Include the following members: Data members: 1) Name of the depositor 2) Account number 3) Type of account 4) Balance amount in the account. Member functions: 1) To assign initial values 2) To deposit an amount 3) To withdraw an amount after checking the balance 4) To display name and balance. Write a java program to print the details of bank account.

Input and Output Format

Refer sample Input and Output

Sample Input

Enter Details:                                                                                                                                  

Accout No: 1234                                                                                                                                 

Name: Raj                                                                                                                                                                                                                      

Account Type: Saving                                                                                                                                                                          

Balance: 50000                

Enter Deposit Amount = 14000                                                                                                                                                                                          

Enter Withdraw Amount = 49000

Sample Output                                                                                                                          

Accout No: 1234                                                             

Name: Raj                                                                                                                                       

Account Type: Saving                                                                                                                            

Balance: 15000
import java.util.*;
public class Bank extends Stud
{
    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter Details:  ");
        System.out.println("Accout No:  ");
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("Name: ");
        String s=sc.next();
        System.out.println("Account Type: ");
        String s1=sc.next();
        System.out.println("Balance: ");
        int n1=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("Enter Deposit Amount = ");
        int n2=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("Enter Withdraw Amount = ");
        int n3=sc.nextInt();
        marks(n,s,s1,n1,n2,n3);
    }
}
class Stud
{
    public static void marks(int n,String s,String s1,int n1,int n2,int n3)
    {
        System.out.println("Accout No: "+n);
        System.out.println("Name: "+s);
        System.out.println("Account Type: "+s1);
        System.out.println("Balance: "+(n1+n2-n3));
      
    }
}
